[0m[48;2;40;67;43m[39m+     46[0m:[39m[48;2;24;38;30m [38;2;191;97;106m-[38;2;191;97;106m The recipe correctly identifies voicemail recordings AND transcripts as PHI ("Voicemail recordings are PHI...Transcripts of those recordings are also PHI. Both are stored in encrypted object storage with customer-managed keys") and correctly elevates the architectural posture: "Audit logs that record voicemail processing should reference the audio and transcript by ID, not embed the raw content; the raw content should live in the secure archive only." This is the right architectural pattern that Recipe 10.1's Finding S1 specifically called out as needing to be elevated; Recipe 10.2 has it right from the outset.[K
