[0m[48;2;40;67;43m[39m+    493[0m:[39m[48;2;24;38;30m [38;2;191;97;106m-[38;2;191;97;106m [38;2;235;203;139m**[38;2;235;203;139mThe KMS encryption-context tagging on the Transcribe Medical output is correct.[38;2;235;203;139m**[38;2;191;97;106m Step 3A's [38;2;163;190;140m`[38;2;163;190;140moutput_encryption_kms_key_id: TRANSCRIPT_BUCKET_KMS_KEY_ID, kms_encryption_context: {voicemail_id: voicemail_id}[38;2;163;190;140m`[38;2;191;97;106m is the correct pattern: the encryption context binds the encrypted-at-rest transcript to the voicemail-id, which the audit trail can verify on subsequent decryption.[K
